A Simple REST-API using Flask in Python

Description:
	A REST API built using flask and flask-sqlalchemy for Database Management flask-marshmallow for serializing data for easy processing.

FULL:
	This basic and complete rest_api can be used anywhere and be devloped more with required features.
	SQL-Alchemy:
		This is a ORM ( Object_Relational_Mapping ) for easy data management without the need of coding SQL Statements into the script.
		The alternative to a SQL Backend is a NoSQl and the best resource is Mongo-Db
	Marshmallow:
		Marshamallow is used for serializing the data to make flow of data more easier
REST-API:
	This REST api has six endpoints with the all the basic and most-used five http methods GET,POST,PUT,PATCH,DELETE

